# Existing Infrastructure Documentation

## 1. Overview

This document provides a detailed overview of the existing infrastructure, which will be used as a reference for creating Bicep templates for cloud migration.

## 2. Network Topology

### 2.1. Diagram
![Diagram]()

### 2.2. Components

- **VLANs**
  - VLAN 10: Office Network
  - VLAN 20: Data Center Network
  - VLAN 30: Guest Network

- **Subnets**
  - Office Network: 192.168.10.0/24
  - Data Center Network: 192.168.20.0/24
  - Guest Network: 192.168.30.0/24

- **Routers**
  - Router1: Cisco ISR 4451, IP: 192.168.10.1
  - Router2: Cisco ISR 4451, IP: 192.168.20.1

- **Switches**
  - Switch1: Cisco Catalyst 9300, Ports: 48
  - Switch2: Cisco Catalyst 9300, Ports: 48

## 3. Servers

### 3.1. Physical Servers

| Server Name | Role            | OS           | IP Address       | Specifications         |
|-------------|-----------------|--------------|------------------|------------------------|
| Server1     | Web Server      | Windows 2016 | 192.168.10.10    | 16GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 500GB SSD |
| Server2     | Database Server | Ubuntu 18.04 | 192.168.10.20    | 32GB RAM, 8 vCPU, 1TB SSD   |
| Server3     | File Server     | Windows 2016 | 192.168.10.30    | 16GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 2TB HDD   |

### 3.2. Virtual Machines

| VM Name     | Role            | Host Server | OS           | IP Address       | Specifications         |
|-------------|-----------------|-------------|--------------|------------------|------------------------|
| VM1         | Application     | Server1     | CentOS 7     | 192.168.20.10    | 8GB RAM, 2 vCPU, 100GB SSD |
| VM2         | Test Database   | Server2     | Ubuntu 18.04 | 192.168.20.20    | 16GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 200GB SSD |

